  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Preparation of method statements, proposals, test plans, acceptance plans, and project schedules in collaboration with the Project Manager.</li><li>Assist project manager with daily on-site monitoring, project implementation and scheduling.</li><li>Plan, coordinate, implement, and manage projects (in part or wholly) to ensure timely progress and delivery of goods/services, while meeting budget, quality, and cost requirements.</li><li>Ensure all work is carried out in accordance with approved plans, regulations, and contract specifications.</li><li>Adhere to the safety and quality standards.</li><li>Conduct and participate in project progress meetings; review schedules and milestones.</li><li>Manage the project team’s training.</li><li>Liaise with consultants, clients, and sub-contractors to ensure smooth project execution.</li><li>Prepare and submit weekly/monthly progress reports.</li><li>Ability to read AutoCAD drawings and schematics is an advantage.</li><li>Perform ad hoc duties as assign by superiors.</li></ul><p><strong>Working Schedule:</strong></p><ul><li>5.5 days work week</li><li>8.00am to 5.00pm.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma</li><li>Proficient in written and spoken English.</li><li>Possess a valid Class 3 driving license or Motor-bike license</li></ul>",
